call up 1) If you call someone up, you telephone them. [mainly AM] [V ] When I'm in Pittsburgh, I call him up... [V (not )] He called up the museum... [V ] Sometimes I'd even call up at 4 AM. Syn: call 2) If someone is called up, they are ordered to join the army, navy, or air force. [be ] Youngsters coming up to university were being called up... [V (not )] The United States has called up some 150,000 military reservists. [Also V ] 3) If someone is called up, they are chosen to play in a sports team. -> See also call-up [be ] He is likely to be called up for Thursday's match against Italy...